{
  "question_id": "question-013",
  "title": "Mayor's Constituents",
  "difficulty": "Easy",
  "question_text": "<div class=\"paragraph\">A small town mayor wonders if his town will support a new city hall building in their town. He decides to send a survey to <span class=\"tex2jax_process\">$50$</span> houses in order to get a feel for those who support the building. Only <span class=\"tex2jax_process\">$30$</span> of the households return the survey. </div><div class=\"paragraph\">What is the population of interest in this setting?</div>",
  "image_files": [],
  "choices": [
    {
      "letter": "A",
      "text": "All the mayor's constituents."
    },
    {
      "letter": "B",
      "text": "The\n50\nhouseholds selected for the survey."
    },
    {
      "letter": "C",
      "text": "The\n30\nhouseholds who returned the surveys."
    },
    {
      "letter": "D",
      "text": "The\n50\nsurveys sent out."
    },
    {
      "letter": "E",
      "text": "The mayor"
    }
  ],
  "correct_answer": "<strong>Choice 'A'</strong> is the correct answer. ",
  "solution": "When planning a study, one must know the <strong>population</strong> and the <strong>sample</strong> from which the data comes. The <strong>population</strong> consists of all items or subjects of interest, while the <strong>sample</strong> is the subset of the population selected for the study. \n\nIn the problem, the mayor is trying to gather data about his constituents by sending a survey to a sample of <span class=\"tex2jax_process\"><span class=\"MathJax_Preview\" style=\"color: inherit;\"></span><span id=\"MathJax-Element-7139-Frame\" class=\"mjx-chtml MathJax_CHTML\" tabindex=\"0\" data-mathml=\"<math xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&quot;><mn>50</mn></math>\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"font-size: 114%; position: relative;\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-33496\" class=\"mjx-math\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-33497\" class=\"mjx-mrow\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-33498\" class=\"mjx-mn\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R\" style=\"padding-top: 0.387em; padding-bottom: 0.387em;\">50</span></span></span></span><span class=\"MJX_Assistive_MathML\" role=\"presentation\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>50</mn></math></span></span><script type=\"math/tex\" id=\"MathJax-Element-7139\">50</script></span> households. Therefore, the subjects of interest in this setting would be all the mayors constituents. \n\n<strong>Choice 'A'</strong> is correct. ",
  "distractor_explanations": {
    "B": "<strong>Choice 'B'</strong> is incorrect. The <span class=\"tex2jax_process\"><span class=\"MathJax_Preview\" style=\"color: inherit;\"></span><span id=\"MathJax-Element-7140-Frame\" class=\"mjx-chtml MathJax_CHTML\" tabindex=\"0\" data-mathml=\"<math xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&quot;><mn>50</mn></math>\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"font-size: 114%; position: relative;\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-33499\" class=\"mjx-math\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-33500\" class=\"mjx-mrow\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-33501\" class=\"mjx-mn\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R\" style=\"padding-top: 0.387em; padding-bottom: 0.387em;\">50</span></span></span></span><span class=\"MJX_Assistive_MathML\" role=\"presentation\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>50</mn></math></span></span><script type=\"math/tex\" id=\"MathJax-Element-7140\">50</script></span> households selected to get the survey would represent the sample. ",
    "C": "<strong>Choice 'C'</strong> is incorrect. The <span class=\"tex2jax_process\"><span class=\"MathJax_Preview\" style=\"color: inherit;\"></span><span id=\"MathJax-Element-7141-Frame\" class=\"mjx-chtml MathJax_CHTML\" tabindex=\"0\" data-mathml=\"<math xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&quot;><mn>30</mn></math>\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"font-size: 114%; position: relative;\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-33502\" class=\"mjx-math\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-33503\" class=\"mjx-mrow\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-33504\" class=\"mjx-mn\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R\" style=\"padding-top: 0.387em; padding-bottom: 0.387em;\">30</span></span></span></span><span class=\"MJX_Assistive_MathML\" role=\"presentation\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>30</mn></math></span></span><script type=\"math/tex\" id=\"MathJax-Element-7141\">30</script></span> households who returned the survey would give us the response rate for the survey. ",
    "D": "<strong>Choice 'D'</strong> is incorrect. The <span class=\"tex2jax_process\"><span class=\"MathJax_Preview\" style=\"color: inherit;\"></span><span id=\"MathJax-Element-7142-Frame\" class=\"mjx-chtml MathJax_CHTML\" tabindex=\"0\" data-mathml=\"<math xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&quot;><mn>50</mn></math>\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"font-size: 114%; position: relative;\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-33505\" class=\"mjx-math\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-33506\" class=\"mjx-mrow\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-33507\" class=\"mjx-mn\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R\" style=\"padding-top: 0.387em; padding-bottom: 0.387em;\">50</span></span></span></span><span class=\"MJX_Assistive_MathML\" role=\"presentation\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>50</mn></math></span></span><script type=\"math/tex\" id=\"MathJax-Element-7142\">50</script></span> surveys are the tool used to collect the data. ",
    "E": "<strong>Choice 'E'</strong> is incorrect. The mayor is the person who is running the survey and data collection."
  },
